The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Stone India plans unit in Himachal

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta, May 12: Stone India Limited of the GP Goenka group has entered into agreements with companies in the US and Italy to set up a greenfield project and upgrade technology. 

 The company will set up the greenfield unit in Himachal Pradesh to manufacture locomotive air dryers in collaboration with Wabtec Corporation of the US.

 The company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) that the unit is being set up in Himachal Pradesh to take advantage of the tax holidays. The production capacity of the unit will be 3000 air dryers per year. The collaborator ? Wabtec Corporation ? may also buy back the product at a later date.

 Stone India MD Amit Mondol or Duncan Goenka group chairman G. P. Goenka was not available to talk about the investment in the new plant. 




